I actually own one of the same model.  Sure some of the the newer polymer .380 pistols are not that much bigger, and are lighter, but there is something to be said for the nice feeling in the hand of an all metal super simple designed pistol.   Designed in Italy, where most of the parts were made.  Due to the Gun Control Act of 1968, assembly was moved to Miami, where the imported parts were installed on a U.S. made frame.   Ultra small, but fun to shoot.   Includes one 7 rd. magazine.
